Silence::

She lowered her weapon and put it away.  But the hatred and anger in
her optics would not subside. "Rodimus, as a new member in all this, I
will follow the orders of my superior officer as is it so written in
my programs. But, I have no program that will make me trust a
Decepticon or Predacon, not an Insecticon or Destructicon.  I will not
trust any of them. No matter how you order me to do so....." she
turned and looked at Rodimus to emphisize this one word, "Sir."  SHe
then looked at Megatron. She took a few paces forward so he was right
in front of her. "I have no interest in your story. I do not care what
has happened. I will word with you as I am ordered. I will do what my
commands are. But I will not like you, trust you or serve you.I may be
smaller and lighter than you. I may not have fire power or as many
fighting programs. But I also will not let you make a move without me
watching you. I will make sure I know where you are at all times. Per
orders is seems we will have to work together, but I do not like it.
And I don't like you. "Her words like ice and sharp as razors.   With
her voice synthisizer grinding under her breath, "decepticon."  And
with that, she started to walk out of the room.
